headline: OPEC+ reportedly considering bigger oil output increase in July
summary: Investing.com -- The Organization of the Petroleum Exporting Countries and its allies (OPEC+) may discuss a larger increase in oil output for July than the 411,000 barrels per day (bpd) increases it implemented for May and June, according to a Reuters report on Friday..
